	<section id="changelog:lib">
		<title>Univention base libraries</title>
		<itemizedlist>
			<listitem><simpara>
				The <command>ucs_registerLDAPExtension</command> offers an additional option <literal>--name</literal>
				which can be used to specify the <literal>RDN</literal> of the LDAP object. This can be useful
				if two versions of a UDM  or LDAP extension need to be active simultaniously in the domain,
				e.g. one being only compatible to Python2, but still required for UCS 4.4-based systems in the domain
				and another beeing only compatible to Python3, required for the systems which at some point will
				have updated to UCS 5. This may be useful in preparation to the UCS 5.0 release (<u:bug>52433</u:bug>).
			</simpara></listitem>
		</itemizedlist>
	</section>

